Key Match Events: David Wiese dominated the Super Over, scoring 21 runs and taking 1 wicket
Mehran Khan almost bowled Oman to victory, taking 3 wickets in his first two overs
Ruben Trumpelmann took three wickets in his first two overs
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia started their T20 World Cup 2024 campaign with a win
Oman will be left ruing the chances they put down, with Jan Frylinck being given multiple reprieves
Miscellaneous Highlights: This was the third time a men's T20 World Cup game went to the Super Over and the first since 2012
David Wiese became just the fourth player in men's T20Is to bat and bowl in a Super Over
Others: The match was played in Bridgetown, June 02, 2024, as part of the ICC Men's T20 World Cup
The scorecard showed Namibia 109/6 and Oman 109, with the game tied and Namibia winning the Super Over
